children.subject:
Although it depends on who you take it with, EE 120 usually isn't a great deal of work. The homework usually took around 2-3 hours per week, if I remember correctly, and my semester didn't have discussion sessions. Professor Babak Ayazifar is usually great about working through examples in class, so I needed less out-of-class review than with EE 16B/CS 61B/CS 70. The midterms can be challenging, but they're usually less competitive than the lower division classes so there can be less time spent on that as well.

Although I haven't taken EE 123 myself, from what I've heard from friends it starts off slow and ramps up exponentially. It's a project class, so expect lots of work in the last month or two working on the final project.

history.content: What's the general workload like for these classes, especially compared to lower divs (16b/61b/70)?
